main event: A radar target was observed for 20 minutes on April 17, 1952 in Benton, Pennsylvania.
interesting points: The target was a strong radar return that was very difficult to lock on.
Two F-94 interceptors were scrambled to intercept the target, but the identification was not obtained.
The target was observed at a speed of 210 knots and an altitude of 21°53' miles.
The target was handed off to another station at a latitude of 40°30' feet.
The weather conditions during the sighting were unknown.
